  "issue_title": "[bug] dashboard: Services latency_url uses raw TOML instead of derived status URLs",
  "issue_body": "### Summary\n\nAfter #140 (`api_http_addr`) and #121 (`core_health_url`), `dashboard_service_targets()` in `genie-api` still sets `latency_url` from raw `config.services.core.url` and `config.services.api.url`. That can diverge from bind/proxy helpers when TOML uses shorthand URLs (e.g. `127.0.0.1:4080/api/status` without `http://`), producing wrong or inconsistent latency probes on the dashboard Services table.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Config:\n\n   ```toml\n   [core]\n   port = 3001\n   bind_host = \"127.0.0.1\"\n\n   [services.core]\n   url = \"http://127.0.0.1:3000/api/health\"\n\n   [services.api]\n   url = \"127.0.0.1:4080/api/status\"\n   ```\n\n2. Start `genie-api` (bind/proxy may use derived addresses after #140 / #121).\n\n3. Open dashboard `/api/services` or inspect `dashboard_service_targets()` in `crates/genie-api/src/routes.rs` L228\u2013240.\n\n4. Observe: `latency_url` is still the raw TOML string, not `http://127.0.0.1:3001/api/health` or `http://127.0.0.1:4080/api/status`.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n- `Config::core_health_url()` \u2192 `http://{core_http_addr()}/api/health`\n- `Config::api_status_url()` \u2192 `http://{api_http_addr()}/api/status` (new helper)\n- Dashboard `latency_url` for `core` and `api` rows use those helpers.\n- Default `geniepod.toml` \u2192 no behavior change.\n\n### Actual behavior\n\n`latency_url: Some(config.services.core.url.clone())` and same for `api` \u2014 duplicates probe logic and can mismatch derived bind/proxy URLs. Core proxy already uses `core_http_addr()` (PR #102); only the Services **latency row** lags behind.\n\n### Hardware\n\nNon-Jetson (x86_64 dev / cross-build host)\n\n### JetPack / L4T version\n\n_No response_\n\n### GenieClaw version / commit\n\nv1.0.0-alpha.9 / main @ crates/genie-api/src/routes.rs\n\n### Relevant logs\n\n```shell\n\n```\n\n### Additional context\n\n**Symptom users see:** Actuation/memories proxies may work (they use `core_http_addr()` since PR #102) while the **Services** table still marks `core` or `api` unhealthy \u2014 confusing \u201chalf broken\u201d dashboard.\n\n**Files to touch:**\n- `genie-common`: `core_health_url()`, `api_status_url()` built from `core_http_addr()` / `api_http_addr()`.\n- `genie-api/src/routes.rs`: `dashboard_service_targets()` \u2014 replace `config.services.core.url` / `services.api.url` clones.\n- `genie-api` route tests (~L981+): stop hardcoding `http://127.0.0.1:3000` / `:3080` where config-driven URLs are under test.\n\n**Acceptance (PR):**\n- Custom `[core].port` + stale `services.core.url` \u2192 dashboard probes derived `:3001` URL.\n- Custom API URL / bind \u2192 `api` row matches `http://{api_http_addr()}/api/status`.\n- Default `geniepod.toml` unchanged.\n\n**Timing:** Implement after #121 / #140 (or PRs #122, #142) merge to avoid rebase churn.\n\n**Real Behavior Proof:** `cargo test -p genie-api` + optional manual `curl` to `/api/services` with a dev TOML on two ports.\n\n**Related:** #121, #140, PR #102.",
